-- Oil & Natural Gas to Spend 88 Billion Rupees on Mumbai Field, PTI Reports
-- B y   N a t a l i e   O b i k o   P e a r s o n
-- 2010-10-17T11:57:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-17/oil-natural-gas-to-spend-88-billion-rupees-on-mumbai-field-pti-reports.html
Oil & Natural Gas Corp., India’s
biggest energy explorer, plans to invest 88 billion rupees ($2
billion) to maintain production at its Mumbai High oil field,
the Press Trust of India reported, citing a company official it
didn’t name.  The field is producing 210,000 barrels a day, down from a
peak of 400,000 barrels a day, the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Obiko Pearson in Mumbai at 
 npearson7@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
